CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1779188575
OL,3,CCrew parachute to safety after two US
OL,4,Cmilitary jets collide during air show
OL,6,FIn 2018, a hang glider pilot died in a
OL,7,Fcrash during a performance, and in
OL,8,F2003, a Thunderbirds aircraft crashed
OL,9,Fwhile attempting a maneuver. The pilot
OL,10,Fwas not hurt, and he was able to steer
OL,11,Fthe plane away from the crowd and
OL,12,Feject less than a second before it hit
OL,13,Fthe ground.
OL,15,FThere are roughly 200 air show events
OL,16,Fheld annually in the United States,
OL,17,Fand the industry has been working to
OL,18,Fimprove safety. The last fatal crash
OL,19,Fat an air show was in 2022 when two
OL,20,Fvintage military planes collided at an
OL,21,Fevent in Dallas and killed six people.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
